    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single deficiency (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is acknowledged and documented; the gap is partially mitigated by consistent results across two independent laboratories. All three primary QoIs satisfy the pre-established acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96; percentage difference < 10%). The overall credibility evidence is sufficient to support the intended regulatory submission for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design. Package is recorded under ProfileMinimal with hash for traceability; cryptographic signature is pending completion of the institutional signature workflow and will be appended prior to final submission.",
